item.title: Were can i learn the java used for a 317 delta
item.dc:creator: @ghostly150 ghostly150
item.description:
@ghostly150 wrote:

What I did when I started making my first server was whenever I had a problem or something I wanted to do was use this forum as a resource, using the search button, and sometimes with difficult problems I made a new topic in Server Help. Whenever I learned how to do something, I would use that new thing I learned i.e. adding commands and eventually it stuck in my brain. So my advice to you is to just keep trying and learning about the source as much as you can until it sticks. If you run into a problem, I’m sure the people on this forum will be happy to help, just use the search button before you make a post to see if anyone asked that and got a solution you can use. Good luck!

Edit: Also you can use server tutorials in this forum. That’s where I got a lot of good information and help and didn’t need to ask in server help.
